Class IntMemoryPairIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.datasketches.hll.IntMemoryPairIterator

  • public class IntMemoryPairIterator
extends Object
    Iterates within a given Memory extracting integer pairs.
    Author:
    Lee Rhodes

    • Method Detail

      • getIndex

        public int getIndex()
        In LIST and SET modes, this gets the iterating index into the integer array of HLL key/value pairs. In HLL mode, this is the iterating index into the hypothetical array of HLL values, which may be physically contructed differently based on the compaction scheme (HLL_4, HLL_6, HLL_8).
        Returns:
        the index.

      • getKey

        public int getKey()
        Gets the key, the low 26 bits of an pair, and can be up to 26 bits in length.
        Returns:
        the key

      • getPair

        public int getPair()
        Gets the key, value pair as a single int where the key is the lower 26 bits and the value is in the upper 6 bits.
        Returns:
        the key, value pair.

      • getSlot

        public int getSlot()
        Gets the target or actual HLL slot number, which is derived from the key and LgConfigK. The slot number is the index into a hypothetical array of length K and has LgConfigK bits. If in LIST or SET mode this is the index into the hypothetical target HLL array of size K. In HLL mode, this will be the actual index into the hypothetical target HLL array of size K.
        Returns:
        the target or actual HLL slot number.

      • getValue

        public int getValue()
        Gets the HLL value of a particular slot or pair.
        Returns:
        the HLL value of a particular slot or pair.

      • nextAll

        public boolean nextAll()
        Returns true at the next pair in sequence. If false, the iteration is done.
        Returns:
        true at the next pair in sequence.

      • nextValid

        public boolean nextValid()
        Returns true at the next pair where getKey() and getValue() are valid. If false, the iteration is done.
        Returns:
        true at the next pair where getKey() and getValue() are valid.
